chatgpt_double_star.new_statement: Environmental protection and economic growth should be advanced together by setting clear health- and science-based environmental floors while giving industries flexible, cost-effective options to meet them. Use predictable, staged targets and streamline permitting for cleaner projects, paired with temporary assistance, retraining, and local investment in regions and workers most affected by change. Measuring results transparently—pollution reduced, jobs created, costs controlled—helps keep both natural resources and economic security strong over time.
